      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(tools): surface empty availability group diagnostics via onHiddenDiagnostic callback",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Empty `allOf`/`anyOf` availability groups are authoring errors (malformed descriptors), but the diagnostics returned by `evaluateExpression` are silently consumed by `buildToolPlan` — tools are hidden from the visible plan with no observable signal to the author.\n- Adds an `onHiddenDiagnostic` callback to `BuildToolPlanOptions` so callers can surface authoring errors (empty groups, unsupported signal kinds) at registration time.\n- Wires `auditPluginToolDescriptors` into `resolvePluginTools` and preserves plugin tool `availability` expressions in `capturePluginToolDescriptor` so registration-time audits see malformed descriptors.\n- Adds explicit `AnyAgentTool.availability?: ToolAvailabilityExpression` typing, exports `ToolAvailabilityExpression` from plugin-sdk, and narrows descriptor capture with `isToolAvailabilityExpression` so private metadata objects are not treated as planner expressions.\n\n## Root Cause (full chain)\n\nSymptom: Plugin/core authors define a `ToolDescriptor` with `availability: { anyOf: [] }` (empty group) and the tool silently disappears from the plan with no warning.\n\nLayer 1: `evaluateExpression` in `availability.ts` correctly detects empty `allOf`/`anyOf` arrays and returns an `unsupported-signal` diagnostic with message \"Empty availability allOf/anyOf group\".\n\nLayer 2: `buildToolPlan` in `planner.ts` receives these diagnostics and hides the tool. The `ToolPlan.hidden` array contains the descriptor and its diagnostics, but nothing reads or logs them.\n\nLayer 3: `BuildToolPlanOptions` provides no mechanism for callers to observe diagnostics. The `unsupported-signal` reason code marks authoring errors that should be surfaced, but there is no callback, logger, or event emitter wired in.\n\nRoot cause: The planner has no channel to surface authoring errors back to the registration layer. Empty-group diagnostics are computed but discarded after tool classification.\n\nMissing guardrail: No logging or callback contract in `buildToolPlan` for diagnostics that represent descriptor contract violations (as opposed to runtime unavailability).\n\n## Fix\n\n- `src/tools/types.ts`: Added `onHiddenDiagnostic` to `BuildToolPlanOptions`.\n- `src/tools/planner.ts`: Calls `onHiddenDiagnostic` for each diagnostic that hides a tool.\n- `src/tools/availability.ts`: Added `isToolAvailabilityExpression` shape guard for descriptor capture.\n- `src/agents/tools/common.ts`: Declared `availability?: ToolAvailabilityExpression` on `AnyAgentTool`.\n- `src/plugin-sdk/{index,core,plugin-entry}.ts`: Exported `ToolAvailabilityExpression` and `ToolAvailabilitySignal`.\n- `src/plugins/tool-descriptor-plan-audit.ts`: Audits plugin descriptors at registration via `buildToolPlan`.\n- `src/plugins/tool-descriptor-cache.ts`: Preserves typed `availability` expressions attached to plugin tools when capturing descriptors.\n- `src/plugins/tools.ts`: Runs the audit during `resolvePluginTools`.\n- Tests: planner, audit helper, descriptor capture (including non-expression metadata guard), and `resolvePluginTools` registration warning coverage.\n\n## What did NOT change (scope boundary)\n\n- `evaluateToolAvailability` and `evaluateExpression` signatures are unchanged — they remain pure functions.\n- The `ToolPlan.hidden` array still contains diagnostics (backward compatible); the callback is an additive surface.\n- Runtime availability diagnostics (`auth-missing`, `env-missing`, etc.) are not distinguished from authoring errors in this change — all hidden-tool diagnostics are surfaced uniformly.\n\n## Compatibility\n\n| Scenario | Before | After |\n|----------|--------|-------|\n| Caller passes `onHiddenDiagnostic` | Silently ignored (extra property) | Callback invoked for each hidden-tool diagnostic |\n| Caller omits `onHiddenDiagnostic` | No diagnostics surfaced | No diagnostics surfaced (same as before) |\n| Existing callers of `buildToolPlan` | Unchanged | Unchanged (optional param defaults to undefined) |\n| Plugin tools without `availability` | Unchanged | Unchanged |\n| Plugin tool `availability` is private metadata (non-expression shape) | N/A | Ignored by descriptor capture; no authoring warning |\n\nThis is purely additive — no existing call path is affected.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed:** Empty `allOf`/`anyOf` availability groups silently hide tools with no observable warning to the author.\n\n**Environment tested:** Node v22 on Linux, branch `fix/92361-tool-availability-empty-group-warning`, head `af05d19d3c6`.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n\nPlanner callback proof:\n\n```bash\nnode --import tsx --no-warnings -e \"\nimport { buildToolPlan } from './src/tools/planner.js';\nfunction descriptor(name, overrides) {\n  return {\n    name, description: name + ' description',\n    inputSchema: { type: 'object' }, owner: { kind: 'core' },\n    executor: { kind: 'core', executorId: name }, ...overrides,\n  };\n}\nconst captured = [];\nbuildToolPlan({\n  descriptors: [\n    descriptor('plugin_tool', { availability: { allOf: [] } }),\n    descriptor('another_tool', { availability: { anyOf: [] } }),\n  ],\n  onHiddenDiagnostic: ({ diagnostic }) => captured.push({ reason: diagnostic.reason, message: diagnostic.message }),\n});\nconsole.log(JSON.stringify(captured, null, 2));\n\"\n```\n\nProduction registration audit proof:\n\n```bash\nnode --import tsx --no-warnings -e \"\nimport { auditPluginToolDescriptors } from './src/plugins/tool-descriptor-plan-audit.ts';\nconst warnings = [];\nauditPluginToolDescriptors({\n  pluginId: 'demo',\n  descriptors: [{\n    name: 'cron',\n    description: 'cron',\n    inputSchema: { type: 'object' },\n    owner: { kind: 'plugin', pluginId: 'demo' },\n    executor: { kind: 'plugin', pluginId: 'demo', toolName: 'cron' },\n    availability: { anyOf: [] },\n  }],\n  logger: { warn: (msg) => warnings.push(msg) },\n});\nconsole.log(JSON.stringify(warnings, null, 2));\n\"\n```\n\n`resolvePluginTools` registration path proof:\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/plugins/tools.optional.test.ts -t \"warns when a plugin tool carries an empty availability group at registration\"\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix:**\n\nPlanner callback:\n\n```text\n[\n  { \"reason\": \"unsupported-signal\", \"message\": \"Empty availability allOf group\" },\n  { \"reason\": \"unsupported-signal\", \"message\": \"Empty availability anyOf group\" }\n]\n```\n\nRegistration audit (`resolvePluginTools` owner path via `auditPluginToolDescriptors`):\n\n```text\n[\n  \"[plugins] tool descriptor authoring error (demo/cron): Empty availability anyOf group\"\n]\n```\n\n`resolvePluginTools` integration test:\n\n```text\n✓ warns when a plugin tool carries an empty availability group at registration\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:** Planner callback, registration audit helper, and `resolvePluginTools` integration test all emit the malformed empty-group diagnostic with the expected message when a plugin factory returns `availability: { anyOf: [] }`. Non-expression `availability` metadata on plugin tools is ignored by descriptor capture.\n\n**What was not tested:** Live gateway startup against a real external plugin package with malformed availability metadata.\n\n## Regression Test Proof\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/tools/planner.test.ts src/plugins/tool-descriptor-plan-audit.test.ts src/plugins/tool-descriptor-cache.test.ts\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/plugins/tools.optional.test.ts -t \"empty availability group\"\n```\n\nAll targeted tests pass on head `af05d19d3c6`.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/tools/planner.test.ts` — 8 passed\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/plugins/tool-descriptor-plan-audit.test.ts` — 2 passed\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/plugins/tool-descriptor-cache.test.ts` — 6 passed\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/plugins/tools.optional.test.ts -t \"empty availability group\"` — 1 passed\n- `git diff --check` — clean\n\n## Current review state\n\nNext action: ClawSweeper re-review on head `af05d19d3c6`.\nWaiting on: reviewer label refresh after CI + re-review.\nBot comments addressed: typed `AnyAgentTool.availability` contract with plugin-sdk exports; `isToolAvailabilityExpression` shape guard for descriptor capture; production-path proof and `resolvePluginTools` regression coverage.\n\nCloses #92361.",
